HEADWORD: Bluets
<hw>Blu"ets</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>bluet</ets>, <ets>bleuet</ets>, dim. of <ets>bleu</ets> blue. See
<er>Blue</er>, <pos>a.</pos>]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A name given
to several different species of plants having blue flowers, as the
<spn>Houstonia c⟦oe⟧rulea</spn>, the <spn>Centaurea cyanus</spn> or
bluebottle, and the <spn>Vaccinium angustifolium</spn>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Blue-veined</ent>⟦br⟧
